Because `model` doesn&#39;t exists in Window interface:
https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/blob/v3.6.4/lib/lib.dom.d.ts#L18500

You can access `window.document`, `window.addEventListener()`, etc.

So, you are telling the compiler &quot;let window object to be **any**thing&quot;.

Without the cast &lt;any&gt; the compiler says `Property &#39;model&#39; does not exist on type &#39;Window &amp; typeof globalThis&#39;.`

Another example:

```ts
interface Person {
    age: number;
    name: string
}

let michael: Person = {
   age: 28,
   name: &#39;Michael&#39;
};

michael.age++;
(&lt;any&gt;michael).hasDogs = true; // hasDogs is not a property of Person, so cast michael to be anything
```

You can test it here: https://www.typescriptlang.org/play/#code/O4SwdgJg9sB0C2UIFMA2ACAvOg5ACzVRhwG4g

